1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,440
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:04,520 --> 00:00:07,680
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,200
Sir.

5
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:15,480
The ops team targeting Phoenix
has sent in their intel.

6
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,440
Let me see it.

7
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:24,240
Okay. Here it is, sir.

8
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,280
Shit.

9
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,760
Sorry, sir.

10
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,920
<i>So? How was that?</i>

11
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,560
<i>If you want to catch me,</i>
<i>you'll need to bring an entire army.</i>

12
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,120
<i>But if you want to test me again,</i>

13
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:56,280
<i>I already have</i>
<i>the full list of your spies.</i>

14
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,680
<i>If you want to send more to die,</i>

15
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:02,920
<i>go ahead. I'll be waiting.</i>

16
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Huh? That's it?

17
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:09,200
Duangnet's body is not in here.
Then where the hell is my daughter?

18
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,480
Duangnet.

19
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:37,280
Your daughter has to go
on an important mission.

20
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,080
But you only brought me here to eat

21
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,720
using department money like this?

22
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,280
That's cheap, Dad.

23
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,160
There's no time.

24
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:46,440
The important thing for me isn't food.

25
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:50,960
It's that we get to sit down
and talk face to face, you know?

26
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,040
Same here.

27
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,720
But for this mission,

28
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,600
I'm really not sure that…

29
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,240
Such is the nature of things.

30
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:06,320
One day, if you don't part ways alive,
you part by death.

31
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,640
But if you're going to die,
you must die giving your all.

32
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,960
The nation comes first.

33
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,120
Excuse me, sir!

34
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,480
You have a call.

35
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,360
I already resigned.

36
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,560
What part don't you understand, Tueng?

37
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,040
I understand, sir, but…

38
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,640
I'm not doing this job anymore.

39
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,200
All my team members are dead.

40
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,760
- Everyone has a family. I'm done.
- Wait.

41
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:46,800
Calm down, sir.

42
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,520
I understand.

43
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,600
But you have to take this call.

44
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,200
Who is it? Huh?

45
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,120
Mr. Poramate.

46
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:03,960
The Seven Legends New Genesis Project?

47
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,320
Yes.

48
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:10,800
This is the final mission
of me and Captain Ong-ard.

49
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:14,240
We have to bring the name "Seven Legends"

50
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,240
back again,

51
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:19,240
to protect our beloved Thailand

52
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:23,160
from criminals of every kind.

53
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:27,760
This is the list of the seven heroes.

54
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:30,200
- We've been searching for years.
- Yeah.

55
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:33,720
Every one of them has something
that reminds me

56
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,000
of the original Seven Legends.

57
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:46,360
Tangkuay, you still kept this?

58
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,960
This is Sergeant Dab's scarf.

59
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:59,480
The last thing he left behind

60
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:04,160
before he died ahead of the others.

61
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,200
Pantong.

62
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,160
Yes, sir.

63
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:12,880
With the criminal network
causing you trouble right now,

64
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:16,000
these rogue agents

65
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,720
are your only hope.

66
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:23,720
Use the original Seven Legends
as their example.

67
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:30,680
I'll revive the name
of the Seven Legends, sir.

68
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,880
Whoa…

69
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,800
Sir.

70
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:57,440
This place feels so eerie and creepy.

71
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,560
Oh my!

72
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:02,840
- What?
- Sir!

73
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:06,040
Underwear this bright red?
Someone still dares to wear it?

74
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:10,000
- If you don't believe, don't disrespect.
- Oh?

75
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:14,840
Sergeant Dab was an elite former soldier.

76
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,120
- A champion marksman too.
- Oh.

77
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:20,560
All that red you see everywhere
is his lucky color.

78
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:25,040
If he isn't wearing anything red at all,
that's the day he's fated to die.

79
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,320
Fated to die?

80
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,200
I thought Superman left it
hanging out to dry.

81
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,520
Fated to die, sir?

82
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,800
Red from the fence all the way in here?

83
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:35,480
Then why did his fighting cock farm go
bankrupt and leave him millions in debt?

84
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,200
Go ask him yourself.

85
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,440
Yes, sir.

86
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,320
Hey, Tueng.

87
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,400
Why are we stopping, sir?

88
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,560
I… I think I stepped on a landmine.

89
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:46,600
What?

90
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,360
What landmine? Don't joke, sir.

91
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,320
He's not joking.

92
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,240
It's real.

93
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:02,000
I planted them everywhere
because I knew you'd come.

94
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:05,680
If any of you move even a little,
you'll be blown to mush.

95
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:10,400
ARAK PASUDJAI
CODE NAME: SERGEANT DAB JAMPOH

96
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,720
- Shit!
- Shit!

97
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,400
Shut up!

98
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,560
- If I have money, I'll pay it back myself.
- Oh?

99
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,920
No need to come
all the way here to collect.

100
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,840
Hey, but that's not…

101
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:22,200
So you don't understand human language?

102
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,880
Then let's say our debt is settled. Zero.

103
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,960
- Huh?
- And don't fucking follow me.

104
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,560
I'm gone for good.

105
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:34,400
Thanks for lending me money
to invest in raising fighting cocks.

106
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,560
It taught me that
I should've raised cows instead.

107
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:39,360
Huh. Cows? Even if you raised buffaloes,
you'd still fail.

108
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,800
I'll raise you, then.

109
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:45,960
What does that mean, sir?

110
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:46,920
You're a buffalo!

111
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:47,880
Oh? Really?

112
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:49,600
- Hey, look. What do we do now?
- Hey…

113
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,840
Uh, sir.
Whatever you do, please don't move!

114
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,160
Hey, Sergeant Dab!

115
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,840
- Tueng.
- Yes, sir.

116
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,680
Are you sure this will work?

117
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,840
Of course, sir. I studied disposal.

118
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,440
Bomb disposal?

119
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,320
- Debt disposal.
- You idiot!

120
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,200
This is life or death
and you're still joking?

121
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,280
Calm down, sir. I don't want you stressed.

122
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,400
I'm even more stressed.

123
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,080
Don't worry. This thing's the key.

124
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,920
Come on! Ha!

125
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,240
I've handled it, sir. No problem!

126
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,400
Huh? What?

127
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:26,640
Where are you going? Whoa.
Running like that one-armed swordsman.

128
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,880
Sir! Wait for me!

129
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,800
Hey. Looking for this?

130
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,200
Let's see how you're getting away.

131
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,440
Give it here.

132
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,480
Sarge.

133
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,760
My boss said you don't
have to pay with money anymore.

134
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,640
Then take my helmet.

135
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:08,000
He doesn't want a helmet.
He wants your life!

136
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,840
Hey, hey. It's only 20,000.
You're killing me over that?

137
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,880
These are the debt collectors,
then what about the ones earlier?

138
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:24,880
- Damn it! He went that way! Hurry!
- Hey!

139
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,080
So many bullets.

140
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,920
You got lots of ammo, huh?

141
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:41,880
Come on.

142
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:44,440
All right,
I'll give you the full treatment.

143
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,520
That's Captain America!

144
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,200
Don't promote me. I'm a sergeant.

145
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,280
Then, let's beat him up.

146
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,800
- Come on!
- Go!

147
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,360
Go!

148
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,440
Ow!

149
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:18,480
Don't you get hurt at all?

150
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,440
You don't know the Iron Body technique
I learned in secret for ten years.

151
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,480
Oh, martial arts too?

152
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,280
Go get him.

153
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,560
- You go first.
- Ow.

154
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:30,880
I'll come back next time.

155
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,960
- Let's go!
- Ouch.

156
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,160
My legs.

157
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,560
- Don't come back for it.
- Ouch.

158
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,120
Even with steel…

159
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,920
These assholes kicked hard as hell.

160
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,240
Ow.

161
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,320
Oh.

162
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,520
Who are you guys now?

163
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,080
You beat Boss Chat's men.

164
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:06,000
But Madam Kim's crew?

165
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,200
You're dead.

166
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,880
Gun?

167
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:20,800
Gun? Two guns? That's nothing to me.

168
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:23,880
I think

169
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,720
you should go play somewhere else, kid.

170
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,560
You really messed me up, you bastard.

171
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:09,840
It's me.

172
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,360
I came so you could confirm it yourself.

173
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,680
Your entire past record is in the system.

174
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,240
Press confirm,

175
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,200
and everything will disappear.

176
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:27,080
After that, you'll have
only one name left. Sergeant Dab Jampoh.

177
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,320
That means…

178
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:33,840
my debts to Boss Chat, Madam Kim,

179
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:36,120
Boss Kui, Boss Guang…

180
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,800
Yeah, all gone. Everything disappears.

181
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,360
Phew.

182
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,440
YOUR RECORDS WILL BE GONE PERMANENTLY
CANCEL / CONFIRM

183
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,200
You want me to go to Pha Mok,

184
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:53,800
a city in the mountains?

185
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:58,080
The nation's new economic hope?

186
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,600
It sounds like a dream city.

187
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:05,080
Built by public and private sectors

188
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:09,440
for high-speed rail
and border's economic expansion.

189
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:13,960
But it's full of shady businesses,

190
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:18,120
and it's the last place
all your agents were killed.

191
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,360
About your daughter,

192
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,880
if her body wasn't found,

193
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:37,880
she's not dead.

194
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:41,920
Hey!

195
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,680
Where the hell did you get
a pic of my daughter in bikini?

196
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,040
Your secretary.

197
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:54,880
I need full identification,
scars, marks, everything.

198
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,000
It's been almost a month.

199
00:15:57,080 --> 00:16:01,000
If I find a mangled corpse, at least I'll
be able to identify it's your daughter.

200
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,800
You could've just sent a photo.

201
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,400
I have my own way of proving it,

202
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,840
not getting some skimpy photo
of my daughter.

203
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,200
Damn it, you idiot!

204
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:10,680
If you're that possessive, keep the photo.

205
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:14,800
I've already saved it on my phone.

206
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:18,080
- Hey!
- Hey, hey, hey.

207
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:20,760
Sir, wait!
I need the photo of your daughter to help…

208
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,880
Help what?

209
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,320
Help you.

210
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:28,960
If you're confident I'm the one who can
help you, don't interfere with my work.

211
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:33,520
Watch yourself, Dab.

212
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:37,040
The moment you infiltrate Pha Mok,

213
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,720
we'll communicate
only via encrypted channels.

214
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,960
If you mess up, no one helps. If you die,

215
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,160
everyone will forget the name
Sergeant Dab Jampoh.

216
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:49,640
I know. I won't mess up.

217
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:51,440
But don't forget

218
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,360
what you agreed to with me.

219
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,880
You remember, right?

220
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:04,040
That Seven Legends team nonsense.

221
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:05,160
I'm not doing it!

222
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:10,200
It's a hassle. I work alone.

223
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,640
Yeah. I remember.

224
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:16,240
I'm the director, you know.
I'll put my rank and position on the line.

225
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,880
A deal's a deal.

226
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:25,400
Hey, sir, wait. You haven't seen them all.

227
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,920
There are more photos on your cloud.

228
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:48,800
FOR SALE

229
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,920
What a punchable face.

230
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,600
Yeah.

231
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,760
Think you're cool?

232
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:33,200
VARAKORN SAWASKORN
CODE NAME: KLA TALUMPHUK

233
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:44,920
But overall, I'd say he's…

234
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:49,040
pretty good-looking.
Are you sure this is Phoenix?

235
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,120
- On the right.
- Huh?

236
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,800
Damn it.

237
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:54,680
Hey, on the right.

238
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:55,760
Hey.

239
00:18:57,200 --> 00:19:00,320
You sure this intel's accurate?
The info Director Pantong gave you.

240
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:05,800
THANAKORN SRIBANJONG
CODE NAME: MOH CHERNGMUAY

241
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,640
My bullets are engraved
with scripts from multiple temples.

242
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,080
I don't shoot randomly.

243
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,960
I'm sure. My pork fell out my mouth.

244
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,440
Still eating?

245
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:20,880
You…

246
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:21,960
That way.

247
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,000
What are you looking at over there?

248
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:40,680
Hey, he looks kinda familiar.

249
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,520
Make sure it's him.

250
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,880
If it's him, I'll drag him by the neck.

251
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:48,000
Let me confirm it.

252
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,800
Hey, hey.

253
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,680
Where did he go?

254
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,840
Hey, he knows.

255
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,360
- Hey!
- Huh?

256
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:11,800
How'd it get here?

257
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,800
Why is it here?

258
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,720
You guys are voyeurs or what?

259
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:29,400
Hey, hey.

260
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:31,880
One shot and your heads explode.
Come to Daddy.

261
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:45,360
- Uh.
- Hey, don't be stubborn. Come here.

262
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,520
Back up. Back up.

263
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,600
Fast hands, huh?

264
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:50,560
You're so hard to tame.

265
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:55,960
- You like peeking through holes, perverts?
- Bro.

266
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:58,000
- What? Stay still.
- Ow!

267
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,000
It's so wild around here.

268
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:16,080
I just got here
and I was about to get my head smashed.

269
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:17,640
No…

270
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:19,320
But your boss messed up.

271
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,440
If he wants to take me out,

272
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,480
he needs to send the top dog.

273
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,960
What?

274
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,240
You talk a lot. Wanna be the top dog?

275
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,560
Not afraid to die?

276
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:37,680
- I'll blow your head up.
- No…

277
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,600
I'll start with you.

278
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:54,280
I need to keep one of you alive
to extract information

279
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:56,520
and trace it back to whoever sent you.

280
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,440
From now on,

281
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:03,000
if I ask something
and don't like your answer,

282
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:04,320
I'll pull the trigger.

283
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:09,160
Who's first? Who? Who's first?

284
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,160
You then.

285
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,440
Talk.

286
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,880
Hey, wait.

287
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,160
- I remember you.
- Huh?

288
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,760
That face. That voice.

289
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:26,920
Slap me again.

290
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,240
What's wrong with you?

291
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:32,480
Harder. One more time.

292
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:33,960
Harder.

293
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:40,000
I remember now. Those slaps. That voice.

294
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,200
Don't you recognize him, Kla?

295
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:49,920
Senior-junior, united as one.

296
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,240
Sai Pradit fights on, never retreats.

297
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,240
<i>Drums echo across Thailand</i>

298
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:59,120
<i>Hearts united, fighting together</i>

299
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,600
<i>Fight together, fight together</i>

300
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,200
<i>Sai Pradit never retreats. We fight!</i>

301
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,480
Too soft.

302
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,120
I wrote that song to fire you up,

303
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,760
not to lull you to sleep.

304
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,800
Anyone sings softly
or gets the lyrics wrong,

305
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,520
I'll slap every one of you.

306
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,600
Do you know

307
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:17,080
what I went through
to lift Sai Pradit Technical

308
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,400
to the top?

309
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,920
How many wounds I traded,
how much blood and flesh?

310
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:25,440
These scars on my fiery red body

311
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,600
weren't from luck!

312
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:30,480
I heard this scar's from falling off
a pick-up truck taxi, right?

313
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:31,360
I fell off a bus!

314
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,800
- Take this! Take this!
- Ow.

315
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:37,800
You were my idol back then.

316
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,280
You remember now, Kla?

317
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:45,120
Senior-junior, united as one.

318
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,400
Sai Pradit fights on, never retreats.

319
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:49,640
Drums echo across Thailand.

320
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,960
Shut up!

321
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:54,120
Yeah! Yeah!

322
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,560
What is wrong with you two?

323
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:57,680
It really is you.

324
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:01,680
Damn, bro. Ever since
you turned your back on the mechanic world

325
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:03,160
and went to serve in the military,

326
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:06,040
we followed your path
to become civil servants like you.

327
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,320
- Mm.
- Yeah.

328
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,120
Amazing. It's really you.

329
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:10,640
Whoa.

330
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:11,800
Civil servants?

331
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:18,040
So you're not the ones
Phoenix sent after me.

332
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,520
No, bro.

333
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:25,440
Then that means you're not
the Phoenix we're looking for, right?

334
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,720
You're looking for Phoenix?

335
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:33,680
Then who are you? Who sent you?

336
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:36,840
Hey!

337
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:41,480
- That's it? Not that impressive…
- Woo.

338
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:42,400
No, wait…

339
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,840
Don't. I'll handle it.

340
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,680
- Go for it, bro.
- You messed them up bad.

341
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:48,000
Let me give you a hard one.

342
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:51,600
- Yeah!
- Woo!

343
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:55,240
- Hey!
- Stay put. Here's another one.

344
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:57,760
- Here!
- Yeah!

345
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:59,640
- Here!
- Whoa. Hey!

346
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:01,760
I said stop!

347
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:03,920
Huh?

348
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:12,280
Just because he's a star senior
from vocational school, you believed him?

349
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:17,240
CHAKRIT BOONSING
CODE NAME: AKKI MEKYANT

350
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:24,840
Maybe he quit the civil service
and became a hitman for Phoenix.

351
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:29,440
NATTAPON RAIYAWONG
CODE NAME: DAN MAHITTHA

352
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:33,200
- Yeah?
- But he kinda fits the description

353
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,840
Director Pantong gave us.

354
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,440
Hm? Are you crazy?

355
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:40,160
No way. He's one of Phoenix's hitmen.

356
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:59,520
Just this rope? Pathetic.

357
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,760
You beat me, huh?

358
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,640
What, you don't believe me?

359
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,800
Fine. Here.

360
00:26:14,480 --> 00:26:16,320
I'll pry his mouth open myself.

361
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,000
What a drag.

362
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,400
- Hey!
- Hey!

363
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:25,840
- There, there, there!
- Ugh.

364
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:29,120
You can't beat my bullets.

365
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:31,640
Or you want me to blow up your pal's head?

366
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,520
So you guys are not Phoenix.

367
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,320
I'm not either.

368
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,840
So who's your boss?

369
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:06,600
You gonna answer nicely,
or you want me to hit you one by one?

370
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,640
- Hey.
- Hey, hey, hey.

371
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:13,760
Don't answer it!

372
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,000
I'll do it.

373
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:20,600
Not mine.

374
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:27,440
- Uh.
- Oh.

375
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:29,720
Why is your phone soft?

376
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:32,600
That's little Akki.
The phone's in the back pocket.

377
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,120
Ayo.

378
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,760
Oh? Sergeant Dab.

379
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:46,840
So you found your team already?

380
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,400
Damn it, Director!

381
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:54,400
<i>Come on, Sarge. No need to yell.</i>

382
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:57,880
I told you this mission is too big
for you to handle alone.

383
00:27:57,960 --> 00:28:00,160
That's why you need a team to support you.

384
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,640
But we had a deal.

385
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,520
<i>If I told you everything,</i>

386
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:07,600
<i>I couldn't appoint you as the leader of</i>
<i>the Seven Legends as Mr. Poramate's order.</i>

387
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,560
<i>Then this mission wouldn't even happen.</i>

388
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:14,520
So I arranged for you to meet your team
to test each other a little.

389
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:15,440
Well? You like it?

390
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:19,320
Desk-bound bureaucrats are all the same.

391
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:21,240
Lying all day long.

392
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:26,600
<i>Mr. Poramate has his reasons for</i>
<i>bringing all of you together as one team.</i>

393
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,840
<i>At first, I had doubts too.</i>

394
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:33,520
But after checking everyone's background,
history, and connections, I understood.

395
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,720
This isn't a coincidence.

396
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:41,480
Sarge, I believe
what Mr. Poramate believes.

397
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:45,600
This is another chance for you,
and for all of you.

398
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:48,120
I don't care.

399
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:55,040
- Sir, we're totally lost right now.
- Yeah.

400
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,880
<i>Sergeant Dab is the team leader</i>
<i>of the Seven Legends.</i>

401
00:28:57,960 --> 00:29:00,920
<i>All of you will work under his command.</i>

402
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,880
- Team leader?
- Team leader?

403
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:09,920
We just stomped him.
How is he the team leader?

404
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,600
I kicked him full force.

405
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,480
Give it to me.

406
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:17,040
He's gone, sir. He's not joining.

407
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:19,560
Don't worry about that.

408
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:22,680
There's an important mission
all of you must handle now.

409
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:25,200
As for Sergeant Dab,
I'll deal with him myself.

410
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:27,720
What mission, sir?

411
00:29:56,720 --> 00:30:00,320
BURANRAT HOMBUT
CODE NAME: TANGKUAY SAELEE

412
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:40,760
- Come here.
- What?

413
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:41,680
Look.

414
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:47,400
KANTAMET RAWINANKOSIN
CODE NAME: JUK BIAWSAKUL

415
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:50,760
Damn, military weapons.

416
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:52,440
Drugs, everything.

417
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,320
Waiting for a saint to come save you?

418
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,760
If we move now, we can still make it.

419
00:30:58,680 --> 00:30:59,920
I checked the route.

420
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:02,840
Heading out north of the forest,
we should reach the rendezvous point.

421
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:09,000
Are you too scared to walk?

422
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,360
- No.
- Oh.

423
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:13,520
Give me your spare magazine. Now.

424
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:15,160
For what?

425
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:17,400
That drug shipment's huge.

426
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,960
I don't want it
slipping into dealers' hands.

427
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:23,320
What? Our main mission's
already blown to hell.

428
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,680
Don't try to look cool.

429
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:30,920
If you've never watched the innocent
die right in front of you,

430
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,040
stay out of it.

431
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:35,920
God knows how many have died
because of this damn drug.

432
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:40,000
That's the spirit. All right, let's do it.

433
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,720
Respect.

434
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,760
I'm not helping you because I want to.

435
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:50,480
You have to survive
so I can get even with you later.

436
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:55,200
Get even later?
What the hell are you talking about?

437
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:57,640
Don't pretend you don't remember.

438
00:31:57,720 --> 00:32:01,880
You and Dan were Wat Krading kids,
rivals with Wat Mayom, my school.

439
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:04,320
At the Four-School football match,
you brought your crew to wreck us.

440
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,560
We couldn't run, so we got beaten to hell.

441
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:09,040
Is now the time to dig up the past?

442
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,200
We'll settle it after this.

443
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:20,120
I'll handle those guys. As for you,

444
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:22,880
you'll have to take a risk.

445
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:27,280
What a waste of my time.

446
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,760
Sarge. Sarge.

447
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:34,680
There are still two of us in the woods.
We have to go help them, Sarge.

448
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:37,800
Sarge.

449
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,000
Sarge!

450
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:43,520
Don't push it.

451
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:46,200
I don't want
to be responsible for anyone's life.

452
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:49,680
Just like before, Sarge.

453
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,560
When you led everyone into fights

454
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:53,640
and you were the only one who made it out.

455
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,520
Your friends all died.

456
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:59,200
So you turned your back on the scene
and joined the military, right?

457
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:13,880
Sarge.

458
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,640
You really won't help?

459
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,560
Please, Sarge!

460
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:59,080
<i>Are you sure you're really going to</i>
<i>let your team throw their lives away?</i>

461
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:00,880
<i>You can help, but you won't?</i>

462
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:05,560
- I'm not forcing anyone. They chose it.
- That's right.

463
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:09,120
At first glance, it looks like the six
of them took the mission for money.

464
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:14,080
But if you know the words

465
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:16,280
"second chance,"

466
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:20,960
that's what you and all six of them
have been searching for their whole lives.

467
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:22,679
And it matters more than money.

468
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:24,520
Enough! I don't wanna hear it!

469
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,520
It won't be a waste of time, Sarge.

470
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,679
This is a secret mission anyway.

471
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:33,120
If you let them die or disappear,
no one will complain, no one will know.

472
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:35,840
But you might regret it later.

473
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:40,639
It's like finding a top-tier escort
and not booking her.

474
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,320
How does he know I hire escorts?

475
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:46,080
You talk too damn much!

476
00:34:47,639 --> 00:34:50,360
<i>All right.</i>
<i>I'll send you the profiles of all six.</i>

477
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,040
Tony. Tony.

478
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:02,080
Tony.

479
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,640
<i>Tony. Tony.</i>

480
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:14,920
Come out. I said come out.

481
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:27,880
Search him.

482
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:30,920
Search? Search what, bro?

483
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,040
Ow, that tickles.

484
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:33,200
Hey, he's got a gun.

485
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:34,800
Where'd a gun come from?

486
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:36,880
Huh?

487
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:39,400
Hey, this is Tony's radio, isn't it?

488
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,840
You took my friend down already?

489
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:45,400
Hey, beat him.

490
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:46,800
- Go over there.
- Come here.

491
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,640
- Come here.
- Whoa.

492
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:50,640
Easy, bro, easy.

493
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:55,640
Hey!

494
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,960
Punch my bro all you want.
It won't hurt him.

495
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:05,240
Why are you so late?

496
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:07,920
I knew you wouldn't die easy, bro.

497
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:10,320
Damn you…

498
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:16,160
What? Confused how I got here?

499
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,240
See what's in my hand?

500
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:22,880
Ha!

501
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:24,720
Not yet.

502
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,960
Ha!

503
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,320
Just kidding.

504
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:33,560
One. Two.

505
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:35,720
Three.

506
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:37,320
Ha…

507
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:39,560
Oh.

508
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:43,520
You messed with me earlier, didn't you?

509
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,520
All that and you're still alive?

510
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:50,160
I'm hard to kill!

511
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,560
This time,

512
00:36:57,640 --> 00:36:58,760
you die!

513
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,680
Delivery's here!

514
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,520
Grenade!

515
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:11,920
Hey!

516
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:12,840
Hey, go!

517
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,320
Hey!

518
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:30,120
Die now!

519
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,720
- Grenade!
- Grenade!

520
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:48,760
Grenade!

521
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,000
Sarge.

522
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,720
Sarge?

523
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:17,800
You!

524
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:40,280
<i>That's Ms. Duangnet,</i>
<i>Director Pantong's daughter.</i>

525
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,760
And the guy next to her

526
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:45,960
is suspected to be part
of the Phoenix network.

527
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:47,920
So that means…

528
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:49,520
Ms. Duangnet is a mole.

529
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:53,080
<i>Don't tell me you're going to deal</i>
<i>with Pantong's daughter alone, Sarge.</i>

530
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:58,120
Watch closely.
You'll see how the veteran does it.

531
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:08,360
This is the Seven Legends team?

532
00:39:08,440 --> 00:39:09,840
Hey, you mole.

533
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:37,680
He's not joking. It's real.

534
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:40,000
I planted them because I knew you'd come.

535
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:44,000
Like "Damn it."
Like you're about to talk over there.

536
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:46,120
- Yeah.
- But this guy just appeared.

537
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:49,560
There. There. Leg.

538
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:50,560
Bang.

539
00:39:50,640 --> 00:39:53,880
Head, pow. Up. Cut.

540
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:08,840
Drum! D-R-U-M.

541
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,640
Roll your tongue. R round.

542
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:13,080
Drums echo. Again!

543
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:16,360
You know "Dab the Crimson," right?

544
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,920
You got lots of ammo, huh?

545
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,400
I'll give you the full treatment!

546
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:26,400
Hey, that's Captain America.

547
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:28,640
Don't promote me.

548
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,200
Come on.

549
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,400
Cut. Okay.

550
